cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of pancreas segmentation in CT scans using deep learning methods. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel model-driven approach that incorporates prior knowledge regularization and a stack scheme for capturing 2D and 3D context information, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of a bi-directional convolutional long short-term memory network also indicates a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
